est a brochure or consultation download a free ebook subscribe to a newsletter or take advantage of a limitedtime discount sign up with bing ads to get started amnioexcel  derma sciences skip to main content united states canada europe middle east and africa emea asia pacific and latin america apla derma sciences regions map select your location from over  countries where derma sciences operates toggle navigation products novel technologies amnioexcel amnioexcel header toolsapplications please contact us general info    customer service  csdermasciencescom  reimbursement   fax  email reimbursement download pdf form amnioexcel dehydrated human amnionderived tissue allograft with intact extracellular matrix about amnioexcel® giving new life to complex wounds amnioexcel® amniotic allograft membrane is a novel human placentalbased tissue product the membrane forms a protective covering over the wound while providing the key components found in human amnion including an intact ecm extracellular matrix cytokines and other growth factors it easily integrates into the wound and helps provide the optimal environment to repair reconstruct and replace wound tissue amnioexcel® is a minimally manipulated amniotic membrane donated by prescreened mothers during planned csections the membrane is dehydrated using the proprietary dryflex™ process which keeps the tissue intact and malleable gives it a five year shelf life at room temperature and retains the key components of human amnion it is intended for homologous use as a wound covering to aid in closing chronic wounds multicenter rct demonstrates amnioexcel®  soc significantly increases closure of chronic diabetic foot ulcers video of tkhxeeuma download information sheet a next generation amniotic allograft suspension about amniomatrix® amniomatrix® is a cryopreserved suspension allograft derived from the amniotic membrane and components of the amniotic fluid it is cryopreserved using the patented cryoprime™ processing method that preserves the structural properties of the collagen cytokines growth factors ecm and viable cellular materials the liquid based suspension is especially suited to help repair wounds where membrane products might not be as effective ie tunneling or deep wounds amniomatrix® is intended for homologous use to help supplement the recipient’s tissue and aid in the closing of chronic wounds download information sheet amniotic tissue products view amnio products amniotic tissue webinars best practices for treating dfus webcast by dr abdopresenter dr raymond abdo dpm fapwca date of video march   video length  minutes  seconds experts agree that total contact casting is the preferred method for offloading diabetic foot ulcers dfus but even with this treatment complicated wounds do not always heal on this webcast we will review the evidence behind offloading and when to use advanced modalities detailed evidence from multiple randomized controlled studies will be reviewed as well as a large prospective case series involving the use of both tccez® total contact casting system and amnioexcel® amniotic allograft membrane on complicated wounds after viewing this webcast we hope that you have a better understanding of the latest evidence of the most cost effective care for your patients with dfus video of ixgjflntqa download video view more webinars and videos amnioexcel® and amniomatrix® are registered trademarks of biod llc derma sciences  a tissue regeneration company skip to main content united states canada europe middle east and africa emea asia pacific and latin america apla derma sciences regions map select your location from over  countries where derma sciences operates toggle navigation select region × welcome to the derma sciences website for europe middleeast and africa view website × welcome to the derma sciences website for canada view website × welcome to the derma sciences website for asia pacific and latin america view website medihoney homepage slide content glob