nated dressings wound cleansers total contact casting featured product info the use of medihoney hcs for the treatment of cancer patients   january  patient dan porter mbe head of sport services facilities directorate at sheffield hallam university shares his story and battle with radiation dermatitis as a result of radiation treatment he was undergoing at times the dermatitis was so severe he didn’t think he could go on medihoney® hcs was able to provide him comfort and wound healing and is proud to share his story read more diabetic foot ulcer solutions   october  diabetic foot ulcer solutions – taking revolutionary steps in diabetic foot ulcer treatment strategies highlights how each of our products support the various stages of dfu diabetic foot ulcer healing and demonstrates how each product can work independently or synergistically to lead the patient down the pathway to wound closure read more barnsley patient saved from amputation by pioneering technology   december  type  diabetic nigel brooke  from royston could have faced the prospect of amputation to his lower limbs due to the effects of a foot ulcer but is now back on his feet after just four weeks thanks to a new technology being pioneered in barnsley lead podiatrist sarah may poppleton suggested a new type of total contact cast called the tccez® – a total contact casting system total contact casting is considered the gold standard of care for offloading diabetic foot ulcers read more the tccez healing chamber   october  in this webcast you will learn not only the history and evidence for total contact casting and what is happening under the cast but also ways to stop the wound escalation and help improve diabetic foot ulcers healing in your practice read more bioguard mechanism of action   july  when managing your patients’ wounds stand guard against opportunistic pathogens that can lead to infection by using bioguard®  a full line of nonleaching nontoxic nonresistant barrier dressings read more download derma sciences full product guide medihoney  derma sciences skip to main content united states canada europe middle east and africa emea asia pacific and latin america apla derma sciences regions map select your location from over  countries where derma sciences operates toggle navigation products novel technologies medihoney medihoney header toolsapplications please contact us general info    customer service  csdermasciencescom  reimbursement   fax  email reimbursement download pdf form medihoney global leading line of medicalgrade honey products for the management of acute  chronic wounds and burns history and heritage of honey in wound healing the use of honey for healing goes back thousands of years to ancient greece and egypt in recent years a resurgence in the science and use of honey has driven research and clinical testing to understand the healing properties and effectiveness of medicalgrade honey in wound healing most specifically the leptospermum species or manuka plant has shown to produce a unique honey optimal for wound healing as a result clinicians worldwide are championing the use of medicalgrade honey across the spectrum of care about medihoney® medihoney® is the global leading line of medicalgrade honey products for the management of wounds and burns derived from the leptospermum species of plant in new zealand these unique dressings have properties which are beneficial throughout all phases of wound healing medihoney® offers a full line of dressing solutions providing versatility for varying wound and wound management needs what is medihoney® with active leptospermum honey medihoney® is an advanced wound care dressing that is supported by over  pieces of evidence demonstrating its clinical ability to promote the removal of necrotic tissue and advance a wound toward healing in a randomized controlled trial the mean healing time was significantly faster for wounds treated with medihoney® impregnated dressings when compared to conventional dressings video of gaqjlidswy indications under the supervision of a healthcare professional medihoney® dressings with active leptospermum honey provides a moist environment conducive to wound healing and is indicated for lightly to moderately exuding wounds such as diabetic foot ulcers leg ulcers venous stasis ulcers arterial ulcers and leg ulcers of mixed etiology pressure ulcers  sores partial and full thickness st and nd degree partial thickness burns donor sites and traumatic and surgical wounds medihoney® products view medihoney products view medihoney products testimonials medihoney® has been a lifesaver i have uncontrollable diabetes and have experienced many painful nonhealing wounds on my feet which at times have required me to be in a wheel chair from the very first time my doctor used medihoney® it made a difference my wounds cleaned up and got better this product is one of the reasons i am mobile and back on my feet again susan medihoney® webinars videos limb preservation awaken the wound for proper healing with medihoney® presenter dr anthony tickner dpm faccws fapwca fapwh fadfs reconstructive foot surgeon and global wound consultant date of video november th  video length  minutes  seconds power webinar image the pathology of a diabetic foot ulcer is complex and if not properly managed places patients at risk for amputation in the us amputation rates are staggering  and mortality rates associated with amputation are as high as some cancers join dr anthony tickner dpm faccws fapwca fapwh fadfs reconstructive foot surgeon and global wound consultant at saint vincent hospital in worcester ma for a clinical discussion on how medihoney® has helped dr tickner awaken wounds stuck in vicious nonhealing cycles to work synergistically with other advanced therapies for successful healing video of ynxdddeqk download video download pdf view more webinars and videos view first video date of video sept   video length min sec medihoney® mechanisms of action video descri